* [[Persi Diaconis]] and Joseph B. Keller. [http://www-stat.stanford.edu/~cgates/PERSI/papers/fairdice.pdf "Fair Dice"]. ''The American Mathematical Monthly'', 96(4):337–339, 1989. (Discussion of dice that are fair "by symmetry" and "by continuity".)
* Bias and Runs in Dice Throwing and Recording: A Few Million Throws. G. R. Iverson. W. H. Longcour, and others. Psychometrika, Vol. 36, No. 1, March 1971
* [[Reiner Knizia|Knizia, Reiner]] (1999). Dice Games Properly Explained. Elliot Right Way Books. ISBN 0-7160-2112-9.

